channel.title: RSTracker
channel.description:
Wow yes I got bored yesterday so I restarted it with nothing and finished it now (10:00PM -> pizza -> 11:00AM -> fap -> 12:00AM -> lost focus/fap -> 4:08 AM -> 4:51 finished post -> PIZZA) Lol'd (im serious i laughed out loud)
[b]How it works: I't download the loader.jar then hooks the file listing classes and cross checks local files with the sha1 list provided in the loader and if it does not exist on the local filesystem it downloads it and archives.[/b]
Example output WIHTOUT a archiving system:
[code] loader.jar cd5e233fa2d61fc116563edecab729e3 11/28/2009 4:26:49 AM unpackclass.pack f150cfcc728ea083f27123647935aba8 11/28/2009 4:26:50 AM runescape.pack200 2470f819f6001bb21b41d9a7a403c9ab 11/28/2009 4:26:57 AM runescape.js5 c8c05b4160801ba4ef771b1664d80436 11/28/2009 4:27:04 AM jaggl_0_0.lib e4342941a3f40438c6370765f8fb8694 11/28/2009 4:27:04 AM jaggl_1_0.lib bce354e0f6f6f606e8f7b65e57ed03fe 11/28/2009 4:27:05 AM jaggl_1_1.lib eddc5123de9c9083795ad522994448e 11/28/2009 4:27:06 AM jaggl_2_0.lib 57c9ca634ac2bd288e4f7a64bf01b978 11/28/2009 4:27:07 AM jaggl_3_0.lib 5ce42064c24cc9f898d0cfb63ce5fa5c 11/28/2009 4:27:08 AM jaggl_4_0.lib 5c91c9b80b265e25dd8ba9f54cffefb6 11/28/2009 4:27:09 AM jaggl_5_0.lib 5dc6c64d3ef09443ba53c8a329a1617d 11/28/2009 4:27:10 AM jagmisc_0.lib 2cceff9df16fe23ae246065182e0e6 11/28/2009 4:27:10 AM jagmisc_1.lib b1cf4dbf6ce79bafebc80b332e431246 11/28/2009 4:27:11 AM jagmisc_2.lib e8c2e04c233034ef6a7788796b6bcb5f 11/28/2009 4:27:12 AM [/code]
I left information regarding setting up archiving the the archive (rstracker.zip) as "readme.txt". Please do not ask questions that which are anwered in readme.txt or this post.
[b][font=Verdana]90% of all of the text following this message will be smarttalk (or as i say, bullcrap)[/font][/b]
don't complain about my code because you can translate logic as well as others and or have bad memory (..............in your head..............).
IMPORTANT: in order to set up ACTUAL file archiving system you will need to do that yourself. i provided the proper things in the "void archive(String name, byte[] data, byte[] sha1)"and "boolean archived(String name, byte[] sha1)" methods. I'm sure you can understand that. If you can't you can either cry about it, call my hotline, OR (heres the big one) read my code (have a problem with that? then please repeat the 3 steps i listed, or leave).
[b]SO IF YOU DECIDED TO SKIP THAT LAST PARAGRAPH:
ARCHIVING CAN BE SET UP IN
"void archive(String name, byte[] data, byte[] sha1)"
AND
"boolean archived(String name, byte[] sha1)"[/b]
To change the RS2 world address host (Ex: world80.runescape.com) change the command line provided argument in run.bat
heres a nice thing: change the "java" argument to "start javaw" and remove the puase and u should get a background service : Yup even i know what 2 + 2 is, 5.
if you dont have your server vm in your java home either move it in they're from a jdk home OR change the server argument to client (or remove it for all i care).
if you experience memory shortage in the program (it shuts down because it cant alloc any more memory on the jvm) i havent needed to run it with more then 2mb. if u do have problems maybe you should change the max memory. (wow, captain ovious)
[b]Dont like it? take it up with my complaint hotline:[/b] [img]http://georgeindenver.files.wordpress.com/2007/10/intelligent-design.jpg[/img]
[b]hotline is 1-800-FIX-MY-TROLLING, IMPORTANT: first call is FREE![/b]
(last part was a joke, or maybe you should call that hotline?)
[i]Have any non violent, ignorant, or stupid questions feel free to ask me them.[/i]
This was a funny but yet 'smartalec' post. One of my best.
